---

layout: recipe
title:  "Florentine with Spinach and Parmesean"
image: florentine.jpg
imagecredit: 
tags: breakfast, eggs

ingredients:
- 5 eggs 
- salt
- pepper
- red chili flakes
- 2 tsp vegetable oil
- 2 cups of baby spinach
- mozarella cheese shreds
- parmasean cheese

directions:
- crack four eggs and whisk together with salt, pepper, and red chili flakes. You can get creative with spices here.
- Heat a frying pan with 2 tsp vegatable oil and add in your eggs
- Scramble eggs for about 1 minute and add in mozarella cheese and baby spinach.
- Cook until eggs are done, about one minute
- Sprinkle with parmesean cheese and additional red pepper flakes (if desired)

---

Based on [Bon Apetit](https://www.bonappetit.com/recipe/scrambled-eggs-with-spinach-parmesan?srsltid=AfmBOorbNNtOUaSrFEXPyeimDu_UjiRwiWc2wGIe9ykOV6_n9UXo6Kzd).
